&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The current implementation of &lt;tt&gt;ClassFinder&lt;/tt&gt; will close a &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; that was opened prior to loading Groovy classes. Specifically, if an application opens a &lt;tt&gt;FileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; for a JAR on the classpath that contains Groovy classes and then subsequently loads a Groovy class contained within, then the underlying &lt;tt&gt;ZipFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; is closed by &lt;tt&gt;ClassFinder&lt;/tt&gt; and the original application receives a &lt;tt&gt;java.nio.file.ClosedFileSystemException&lt;/tt&gt; on subsequent operations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
